<font color="#FF0000">LUNCH FROM &quot;THE LITTLE COMMIE&quot;</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jul 25 21:10:31 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook, I will decline lunch with you. In fact, I rarely eat with anyone who refers to me as &quot;a little commie&quot;. In fact Cook (is that your real name or just your job?), you will never be in &quot;my neck of the woods&quot; as I tend to think you are some ultra-nationalistic-macho-caveman-gorilla, still spewing out racist hatred 30 years after the fighting ended. <br><br>
I was never a communist, never anything but a true American Patriot. I know you can't understand that. You call yourself the warrior&quot;, I say rather you were the fool. The war is over, the dead are buried, but you have to keep the hatred alive to give your life some meaning, and you  try and mis-use this site to push your wantabe book of memories of hatred. Yes Cook, these are MY Thoughts, and I say you are a hate driven racist-facist, and certainly not a representative of the real veterans of Viet Nam. Those who have grown up and beyond.<br><br>
I've been to the wall, Cook, and I did it in the middle of Little Saigon. And I shared my soul and guts right here. I am rather proud that I am able to learn and grow, and many here have been my mentors.  I absolutely know that you can't make that claim.  Real tough guy. Keep on chasing your ghosts, Cook, because then you won't have to face the fact that you were wrong then, are wrong now, and will continue to be wrong (boy, you must be fuming about now-right?) and the simple fact is you are a racist, smug, hate filled war monger.  Note: I did not call you a baby killer. Your life clearly peaked in Viet Nam and in killing &quot;gooks&quot; and you have never gotten beyond, or over, that. I have helped 100's of vets pick up the pieces and get over the war and on with their lives. Can you say that?  Hell no. Who do you help with your never ending name calling and hatred?  May God help you because I sure won't.<br><br>
It must be nice to view the world in your terms, Cook, that of black and white, good and bad, big and little. Me Tarzan, You Jane. I prefer the reality of color vision, of knowing that there many opinions and views, or colors, on any issue, and that mine is just that, mine. Not some &quot;communist propaganga&quot; puking right wing macho gorilla man. Christ, reading you and Mano y Ramon and I lose my apetite in total. You too sound like either a mutual admiration society, the KKK,  or latent homosexuals who are both too afraid to make the opening pass. Eitherway you are out of date, out of touch, and simply stated, out of it.<br><br>
To my friends of the back channel, I'm sorry. I held back as long as MY HONESTY would allow. I just got fed up with low life guttersnipes hiding behind their keyboard bravado and their off key singing of the National Anthem. Remember it is &quot;MY&quot; National Anthem too. I have had way too much experience with these &quot;types&quot; of individuals, both inpatient and on the street, and I know where their hatred will lead them. I just decided to give it a push.  Their responses will prove me right. They can take their best shots at me, such as it may be, but I know what tripe and dribble it will be.<br><br>
While I am on the issue of responding to bullshit and veteran whinners, let me move on to Arthur V.<br>
Art, one of these days you will have a position that is your own, not someone eles's that you  &quot;me too&quot;.  It gets old to hear you echoing others thinking. Try doing some on your own. One day you are my friend, than another my enemy, Tom's one day, Cooks the next.  Art, you can't play all sides with out getting nailed by one or the other. At least I have ALWAYS struck from the front, not like some trollers on this site who need backdoor bully bravado. Think about it, then post.<br><br>
Tom &amp; Chet: You both are gentlemen, even Chet on Television, and continue to be two of the cleanest thinkers on this site. You both, and others, have taught me much about the &quot;other side&quot; of the Viet Nam war, and the Veteran, and your teaching was solid enought that I can easily overlook the recent attacks by those who still think the communist menance is upon us.  I thank you and I know you will forgive me this lapse of taste and manners. Sometimes you just have to spit it out, and flush it away.<br><br>
